    "description": "Sam Altman recently said that we're about to enter the \"Fast Fashion Era\" of SaaS.\n\nAnd I think he's right.\nI've been calling this the \"Temu Effect\" of SaaS.\n\nThis doesn't mean SaaS is over.\n\nBut it means there are 3 types of SaaS that will dominate, and other types will get squeezed out.\n\n→ Enterprise SaaS\n→ Hybrid SaaS-Agency\n→ Commodity-SaaS\n\nEnterprise SaaS is obvious.\nThey still depend on a lot of human work that can't be easily replaced by AI.\n\nIt's one of the positions I think is somewhat safe.\nHere's what I mean.",
